 ### Downstream durable-deferral format
 
-A session that first records durable deferred work is changed to the fail-closed downstream header type `dev.taylorrowser.pi-wait-for-user/session`, downstream format version `1`, with `basedOnPiSessionVersion: 3`. This namespace prevents unpatched Pi or a future official schema from silently interpreting experimental records.
+Every new persisted session created by this downstream enables durable deferral before its first append. Its first flush therefore uses the fail-closed downstream header type `dev.taylorrowser.pi-wait-for-user/session`, downstream format version `1`, with `basedOnPiSessionVersion: 3` — even if the Agent Thread never defers a tool call. This namespace prevents unpatched Pi or a future official schema from silently interpreting experimental records.
 
 ```json
 {"type":"dev.taylorrowser.pi-wait-for-user/session","version":1,"basedOnPiSessionVersion":3,"id":"uuid","timestamp":"...","cwd":"/path/to/project"}
 ```
 
-Unsupported downstream versions or mismatched base Pi versions are rejected before mutation. Durable deferral is unavailable for in-memory sessions and `--no-session`. See [Durable Tool Deferral](deferred-tools.md).
+This eager conversion is deliberate. Session entries are append-only and immutable, so waiting until the first deferral after ordinary history has flushed would require rewriting the header and introduce a failure window. The compatibility tradeoff is that Stock Pi cannot open any new persisted session created by this downstream, including sessions containing only ordinary prompts and responses.
+
+Unsupported downstream versions or mismatched base Pi versions are rejected before mutation. Already-flushed Stock Pi sessions keep their upstream header and remain readable by Stock Pi, but cannot enable durable deferral. Durable deferral is also unavailable for in-memory sessions and `--no-session`. See [Durable Tool Deferral](deferred-tools.md).
 
